div.h3: Multi-head attention learns diverse retrieval strategies through independent projections

div.p: Each head learns its own W_Q^i, W_K^i, W_V^i matrices:
Q_i = X @ W_Q^i # Shape: [batch, seq, 64] K_i = X @ W_K^i # Different projection different query semantics V_i = X @ W_V^i # Different projection different value extraction
Gradient flow: Each head receives independent gradients, allowing W_Q^1 to learn syntactic queries while W_Q^2 learns semantic queries.
No enforced diversity: Specialization emerges naturally from training the model discovers that distributing patterns across heads is optimal.
Head outputs concatenated, then projected through W_O
